I think that this was a clue/answer that favors the older generations, for whom PEORIA was probably a gimme.  The old trope, "But will it play in PEORIA?", regarding whether a Broadway show would be understood by the "rubes" when it went out on a road tour, has more or less fallen out of use lately, but us olds remember it well.

A show that would play in PEORIA would continue to make money after its original run was done, so that was considered a good thing.

