The clue says [Many SAT takers], not "most".  I think it's accurate to say that Many SAT takers are seniors. In addition to the ones who want to try to do better, there are many who didn't get around to it in junior year.

As to your other nit, assuming you were serious, PEORIA is small, but it's more than double the size of Normal. And Normal's growth has come in recent decades; back in the 30s, around when the phrase "Will it play..." was popularized, PEORIA outpopulated Normal by about 20 to 1.  In order to wonder if something is going to play well somewhere, that somewhere has to be big enough to be worth stopping at in the first place.
